This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with recognizing human actions from skeleton data provided by Kinect sensor. Additionally, the use of deep learning algorithms for feature extraction and classification makes it likely to belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the potential applications of the proposed method in human-computer interfaces, which suggests that it could belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of video datasets for experiments indicates that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
